						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall of the backyard of the Taluk Office.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI—A.D. 1102.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 27, Chitrabhānu. Āshādha, śu. 5, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1102, June 22.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription registers a gift of income from taxes to god Muddēśvara in the temple of Svayaṁbhu-Sōmēśvara at <hi rend="bold">Puligere</hi> by Daṇḍanāyaka, Achchupaṁnāyadadhishṭhāyaka <hi rend="bold">Mādhava-bhaṭṭa</hi> who was a subordinate of Mahāsāmantādhipati, Maneverggaḍe <hi rend="bold">Bhīvaṇayya</hi> who was administering the <hi rend="italic">achchupannāya</hi> tax of Palasige-12,000. The gift was entrusted to Mahēndrasōma-paṇḍita, the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> of the temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="italic">Published in Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, pp. 31 ff.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
